title: Whereas the Parliament stands prorogued untill the seventeenth day of January next, and whereas for sundry causes and considerations, we have thought it fit and convenient and necessary further to prorogue the said Parliament untill the twentieth day of February next ... by the Lord Deputy, Ossory.
